%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-mortgage-rates-outlook-prediction-top-cities-homebuyers-owners-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20modest%20victory%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20homebuyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20median%20value%20paid%20up-front%20for%20a%20US%20house%20fell%20to%20%2430%2C300%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20%242%2C400%20lower%20than%20the%20record-high%20rate%20of%20%2432%2C700%20in%20the%20prior%20quarter%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realtor.com%2Fresearch%2Fdown-payment-report-oct-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%20from%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRealtor.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealtor.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20figure%20was%20roughly%209%25%20of%20the%20total%20cost%20for%20a%20median%20home%2C%20up%20from%20a%20stable%20level%20of%205%25%20for%20most%20of%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20so.%20This%20doesn't%20include%20second%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpensive%20properties%20skewed%20the%20average%20down%20payment%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20to%20around%20%2485%2C400%20or%2014.5%25%20of%20the%20total%20price%2C%20said%20Hannah%20Jones%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRealtor.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealtor.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20economic%20researcher%20who%20wrote%20the%20report.%20Buyers%20had%20paid%2014.9%25%20of%20the%20average%20sale%20price%20off%20the%20bat%20from%20April%20through%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20slight%20declines%20suggest%20that%20the%20US%20housing%20market%20is%20cooling%20off.%20Smaller%20down%20payments%20are%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20less%20competitive%20market%2C%20Jones%20noted%2C%20since%20buyers%20don't%20need%20to%20blow%20away%20sellers%20with%20a%20massive%20sum%20of%20money%20up-front.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20down%20payments%20remain%20historically%20high%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20they'll%20fall%20further%20or%20are%20just%20ticking%20lower%20in%20what's%20usually%20a%20quieter%20time%20of%20the%20year%20for%20home%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20too%20soon%20to%20tell%20if%20this%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20downward%20down%20payment%20trend%20or%20just%20a%20slight%20shift%20in%20the%20seasonal%20pattern%20due%20to%20the%20year's%20housing%20market%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4a4ddf9-f936-4d65-b706-3eb1914e5fdb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBorrowing%20costs%2C%20savings%20rates%20sway%20down%20payments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20analysis%20of%20down%20payments%20that%20doesn't%20mention%20mortgage%20rates%20would%20be%20incomplete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-year%20fixed%20mortgage%20rate%20hit%20a%20two-decade%20high%20of%207.8%25%20last%20October%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freddiemac.com%2Fpmms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20steadily%20fallen%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20most%20of%20the%20last%2012%20months.%20Borrowing%20costs%20have%20slipped%20from%20around%207%25%20early%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20to%206.4%25%2C%20anticipating%20and%20responding%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-cuts-interest-rates-how-much-september-fomc-powell-inflation-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20extra-large%20rate%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20rates%20mean%20that%20buyers%20don't%20feel%20as%20much%20pressure%20to%20cough%20up%20as%20much%20money%20up-front.%20Down%20payments%20may%20stay%20subdued%2C%20so%20long%20as%20the%20interest-rate%20easing%20cycle%20has%20steam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20progress%20is%20expected%20to%20continue%20into%202025%2C%20which%20could%20mean%20further%20easing%20in%20down%20payments%20if%20home%20shoppers%20hold%20out%20for%20even%20lower%20mortgage%20rates%20that%20consumers%20widely%20expect%20to%20see%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote%2C%20though%20it%20%26quot%3Bcould%20have%20the%20opposite%20effect%20if%20buyer%20competition%20were%20to%20pick%20up%20once%20again%20as%20falling%20mortgage%20rates%20improve%20home%20purchase%20affordability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwinning-a-bidding-war-top-tips-according-to-realtors-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earen't%20getting%20into%20bidding%20wars%20like%20they%20were%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20the%20rise%20in%20home%20listings.%20More%20inventory%20means%20that%20competition%2C%20and%20down%20payments%2C%20are%20being%20kept%20at%20bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInventory%20is%20growing%20such%20that%20an%20uptick%20in%20demand%20has%20not%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20competition%20so%20far%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20less%20rosy%20explanation%20for%20lower%20down%20payments%3A%20buyers%20can't%20afford%20to%20pay%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20personal%20savings%20rate%20in%20the%20US%20was%204.8%25%20in%20August%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRealtor.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealtor.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20up%20from%20the%20inflation-stretched%20low%20of%202%25%20in%20June%202022.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20well%20below%20both%20the%20typical%20pre-pandemic%20rate%20of%206.5%25%20and%20even%20the%205.5%25%20mark%20from%20the%20start%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lower%20savings%20rate%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20suggests%20that%20buyers%20would%20have%20a%20harder%20time%20saving%20for%20a%20large%20down%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20down%20payments%20are%20roughly%20twice%20as%20large%20as%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Jones%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20nest%20egg%20built%20up%20during%20the%20pandemic%20has%20not%20been%20fully%20depleted%2C%20thus%20there%20is%20still%20excess%20personal%20savings%2C%20likely%20